    <header>
        <product>PP</product>
        <title>PP.MSGPAYMENTTYPECHANNEL</title>
        <table>PP.MSGPAYMENTTYPECHANNEL</table>
    </header>
    <overview>
        <ovdesc>
            <p>This screen is used to define many-to-many relation between Message Payment Type and Channels used in the payments hub.</p>
            <p>A record authorised in this screen will create or amend or reverse a record in store table, PPT.MSGPAYMENTTYPECHANNEL</p>
        </ovdesc>
    </overview>
    <menu>
        <t>
            <field>ChannelName</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the name of the channel.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>Mandatory input. 1-10 alphanumeric characters. Value links to field 'ChannelName' in PPT.CHANNEL.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>ID</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Unique identifier for the entity Payment Message Type Channel.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>i) 35 Alphanumeric characters.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>MessagePaymentType</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the Message Payment Type.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>Mandatory input. 1-10 alphanumeric characters.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>Examples:</p>
                <p>101, 202, BACSCT, ATADB etc</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>OVERRIDE</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during Input. During the validation of a transaction, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>RACMessagePaymentTypeChannel</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Record Activation Code generated for the record by the payment's hub. </p>
                <p>Possible values:</p>
                <p>N - Not active</p>
                <p>A -  Active</p>
                <p>H - History</p>
                <p>F - Future</p>
                <p>C - Not active future</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>19 alphanumeric characters.</p>
                <p>The value is not editable by the user.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>RSCMessagePaymentTypeChannel</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Record Status Code generated for the record by the payments hub.</p>
                <p>Possible values:</p>
                <p>L - Live</p>
                <p>U - Unapproved</p>
                <p>R - Reversed</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>1 alphanumeric character.</p>
                <p>The value is not editable by the user.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
